Durban - Two weeks after President Cyril Ramaphosa opened new offices for the Department of Home Affairs in Hluhluwe, he will open officially open the Kokstad Home Affairs office. The Presidency said the opening of the office on Wednesday, forms part of  the government’s programme to expand the footprint of Home Affairs service delivery points, and meet citizens’ demand for Smart ID Cards and other enabling documents. "By availing these services to marginalised communities, the department plays a key role in enabling and deepening democracy and social justice," said spokesperson Khusela Diko. In addition, President Ramaphosa will hand over 443 title deeds to beneficiaries of the Franklin Housing Project. The government said this formed part of the restoration programme that aims to ensure that the beneficiaries of the government’s housing programme realise the full benefits of owning a house and are brought into the formal property market. The President will be accompanied by Minister of Home Affairs, Malusi Gigaba and Minister of Human Settlements, Nomaindia Mfeketo. Daily News